67762]

Hi Stephen,
Below is a copy of an email which I sent to all parties this afternoon outl=
aying the expected time frames of the results which will be available to be=
 shared with all regarding test results from 23 Mays Street, Devonport.

Prior to receiving the report from the forensic testing =E2=80=93 I am keen=
 to take whatever steps I can to progress the claim.
Preliminary results and findings suggest that we may have a relatively comp=
lete understanding of what the final scope of works will be to fully remedi=
ate the property under the claim.

If we accept on a preliminary basis that the scope of works required to rem=
ediate the property is generally defined as follows:

Basement Level

  *   Clean and decontaminate all exposed internal brick surfaces to ground=
 level of dwelling
  *   Replace charred timber framework to midfloor structure and ground flo=
or walls as required
  *   Rebuild rear deck and steps to match existing
  *   Replace all hardwood decking boards to internal balcony
  *   Clean and encapsulate all timber structural components to ground-floo=
r walls and midfloor structure as required
  *   Replace midfloor insulation
  *   Replace ceiling linings to ground floor as required
  *   Supply and install rear pedestrian door to rear of ground floor
  *   Clean and repaint bi-folding basement doors to ground floor
Second Level

  *   Disconnect, clean, and reinstall existing electrical outlets and fitt=
ings as required
  *   Remove all gib-board linings from the interior of the dwelling =E2=80=
=93 exterior walls only [?]. Ceilings to remain
  *   Clean and decontaminate all interior brick surfaces in the exterior w=
all cavities
  *   Encapsulate all timber framing to all exposed walls
  *   Re-line all exposed walls with new gib-board wall linings. Gib-stop a=
nd sand to L4
  *   Seal and apply 2 topcoats to all new plasterboard linings
  *   Clean and repaint all remaining interior surfaces. Internal doors, ex=
terior joinery, wardrobes, etc
  *   Remove kitchen cabinetry as required to clean and decontaminate any a=
djoining wall surfaces
  *   Strip and refit entire bathroom to allow for decontamination and reme=
diation as required. Reuse existing fitting and fixtures where possible
  *   Clean polished hardwood strip flooring [ no re-coat of polyurethane ]
Roof Space

  *   Remove and replace all existing roof insulation
  *   Encapsulate all timber roof structure framing.
  *   Remove and replace roofing underlay paper
  *   Remove, dispose of existing roof cladding
  *   Supply and install new roofing cladding to match existing
  *   Supply and install new PVC spouting and downpipes
  *   Clean and repaint soffits
  *   Clean and repaint fascia board
  *   Supply and install new central heating unit to match existing =E2=80=
=93 or equivalent
General

  *   Scaffold and shrink wrap dwelling to enable works
  *   Preliminary & General works as required

I will need to discuss the above with you in some detail, accepting that yo=
u may make corrections as required =E2=80=93 however once we have discussed=
 the draft proposed scope I will request that you provide Tower Insurance w=
ith a draft copy of the scope at which we arrive, and an accompanying cost =
estimate for reserving and quoting purposes.
Let=E2=80=99s talk tomorrow when we can.
Many Thanks,
Grant.


