Kia ora Grant,

As discussed on Monday, could you please provide, as soon as possible, the =
full list of tests performed during the 17 October site visit, together wit=
h the raw data as it becomes available, and then the formal reports when is=
sued. This is to accelerate the identification and sourcing of any missing =
tests or gaps.

Please include for the list of tests performed:


  1.  Test name and brief description
  2.  Sampling scope and exact locations (room/area, height, within-cavity =
vs surface)
  3.  Field notes for each sample (date/time, sampler, method, pre/post-cle=
an trial where applicable)
  4.  Photographs tying samples to locations and any before/after decontami=
nation trial images
  5.  Any areas not tested and the rationale

Please include for the test results / raw data:


  1.  As above plus
  2.  Laboratory details for each sample (lab name, job ID/COC, method code=
s, analytes, units, detection limits/LOQs, QA/QC including blanks/duplicate=
s)
  3.  Raw data and Numerical results of each test
  4.  Results of any on-site decontamination efficacy trials (pre/post meas=
urements and method used)

Ng=C4=81 mihi,
Raffaella del Prete


